      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "VALENTIAGO (5) frustrating gelding who can shed his Maiden tag fifth-up today. Expect to see him race a touch closer after he attacked the line strongly when second over 1500m at Goulburn. Hard to hold out. SHAWNEE BOY (4) near his peak for this third-up and gets a much better set up today. Taken back from the wide gate and never looked a genuine threat with a plugging eighth over 1350m at this track. Sharp improver over this distance range and sure to be thereabouts. MOUNTAIN QUEEN (7) resumed in a three-horse race with a game second in the heavy (9) going at Nowra. Another who will appreciate the extra trip with top-three claims. SO D'ORO (8) returned off the two trials with a handy fifth from near last on the turn over 1350m at this track. Will race closer and shapes as one of the leading prospects.",
